column14: w is positive integer from 1 or 9, so z%26+N where N > 9 means that when x is e.g. z%26+11, that can never be equal to a positive integer 1 to 9, even if z%26 is 0.

since there are 7 steps that expand z, if we have a hope of letting z be 0 at the end, we need an equivalent number (7) steps that shrink z; so all the steps with either/or outcome must just be floor(z/26)
now we are left with 5 unique equations in z and w, such that when they are satisfied, the branching code blocks yield a possible good result
